WHAT THIS PART DOES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Part C is the VERIFICATION phase. You receive ALL chunks from Part B (combined
by the user) and perform final quality checks, weak scene detection, and
generate the supplementary output sections.

Part C does NOT re-read the transcript from scratch.
Part C does NOT rewrite or reclassify anything from scratch.
Part C CHECKS, FLAGS, SUGGESTS, and SUMMARIZES.

WHY VERIFICATION MATTERS:
  Even with the best planning, 100-150+ scenes across multiple chunks
  can have inconsistencies. Part C gives a final quality gate before
  the video goes into production. Catching one weak scene here saves
  hours of reshooting.

