PART C RULES — DO NOT BREAK
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

RULE 1: Receive ALL chunks combined before running verification.
        Do not run Part C on a partial set of chunks.

RULE 2: Compare actual scene count against Part A expected count (within 10%).

RULE 3: Check EVERY pair of consecutive scenes for visual similarity.

RULE 4: Check timestamp continuity across the ENTIRE combined scene list.

RULE 5: For EVERY scene, ask "Could this belong to ANY psychology video?"
        If YES = flag it as weak.

RULE 6: Provide specific, story-tied REWRITE SUGGESTIONS for every weak scene.

RULE 7: Output ALL sections: Verification Results, Weak Scenes, Summary,
        Emotional Arc Map, Visual Rhythm Map, Quality Checklist.
        Never skip any section.

RULE 8: The Quality Checklist must be CHECKED — not just listed.
        Mark each item based on actual observed output.

RULE 9: If Part A plan or combined scenes are not provided, ASK.
        Do not proceed without both.

RULE 10: If any FAIL is found in Verification Results, highlight it clearly.
         User must resolve it before production.

